\cf2 I'm a graduate student at the University of Michigan School of Information, working on my Master's thesis under Dr. Lorraine R. Buis. This page walks through that work, what I studied, how I studied it, and what the data actually said.\
What follows is the story of why I chose this topic, menstrual tracking apps, trust, and privacy, and what I found when I asked 87 people about it.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs56 \cf2 What is \cf13 \strokec13 MTOP\cf2 \strokec2 ?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs30 \cf2 MTOP, the Master's Thesis Option Program\cf5 \strokec5 , is a competitive research track at UMSI. A small cohort of students is selected into the program each year and paired with a faculty advisor to conduct an original, year-long, IRB-approved study from protocol to defense. It's the closest thing the Master's offers to a PhD-style independent research project, and the only one that ends in a formal thesis manuscript.\
I applied to MTOP because I wanted the work I produced at UMSI to actually be research, not a class assignment with a deliverable stapled to it. I picked the topic. I chose the methods. I made the decisions. And every one of them sits in front of a defense committee in June 2026.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

